JOHANNESBURG – Police on Monday arrested four suspects in connection with the hijacking of a bodyguard of a Gauteng MEC on Monday. Faith Mazibuko, MEC for Sports, Arts, Culture and Recreation, Faith Mazibuko bodyguard was hijacked on Saturday. A Mercedes Benz ML 500 was recovered. READ: Tshwane mayor Solly Msimanga hijacked “The suspects were arrested in Eldorado Park in the early hours of Monday, 04 June 2018. They were found in possession of the hijacked vehicle, firearm believed to be the one taken from the protector and another unlicensed firearm,” said Police spokesperson, Captain Mavela Masondo. The suspects will be charged with hijacking, kidnapping as well as possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition. READ: Hijacking hotspots in Johannesburg They will appear at Johannesburg Magistrate’s Court in due course. eNCA